article.headline: UC Santa Barbara 68, Pepperdine 57
article.story: SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) -- Alex Harris shot four 3-pointers and scored 22 points to lead UC Santa Barbara to a 68-57 victory over Pepperdine Wednesday. Chris Devine had 10 points and seven rebounds, while James Powell added 13 points for the Gauchos (8-1), who won their sixth straight game. Justin Joyner lead UCSB's defense with six assists and three steals. The team made 9-of-13 shots from the 3-point arc and shot 50 percent overall. Malcolm Taylor led the Waves (4-6) with 13 points. Pepperdine made just 4-of-21 3-balls for the night and shot 38.6 percent overall.
